According to the MoD, Ukrainian forces are continuing to "hold the line" in the Donbas and on Tuesday struck the Antonovskiy bridge over the Dneiper river. The bridge is a key vulnerability for Russian forces as it is one of two crossing points over the Dneiper river that Putin's troops can use to supply or withdraw its troops to occupied territory. The MoD predicts that control of Dneiper crossings is likely to become a key factor in the outcome of the fighting in the region. FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES...